WEBVTT

02:00.537 --> 02:02.205
[RHYTHMIC CLANKING]

02:32.236 --> 02:34.570
SAILOR: Merry Christmas, captain.
JOHN: Merry Christmas.

02:34.738 --> 02:36.739
Merry Christmas, sir.

02:36.907 --> 02:38.908
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

04:14.838 --> 04:17.798
DOCTOR:
Police told you about the child?

04:18.341 --> 04:19.507
Yes, they did.

04:19.718 --> 04:23.346
I'm very sorry,
but we'll need a formal identification.

04:23.555 --> 04:24.722
Yes, of course.

04:24.890 --> 04:26.515
I have to warn you...

04:27.392 --> 04:30.561
...most of the injuries were to the face,
I'm afraid.

04:31.521 --> 04:33.481
JOHN:
The police said that....

04:33.649 --> 04:36.233
That my son died on impact.
Is that correct?

04:36.401 --> 04:38.069
Not quite.

04:38.487 --> 04:40.947
Just after the ambulance arrived.

04:41.114 --> 04:43.366
-And how long was that?
-He was unconscious, captain.

04:43.533 --> 04:47.119
-He wouldn't have been aware of any pain.
JOHN: How long, doctor?

04:47.412 --> 04:49.413
About twenty minutes.

04:55.754 --> 04:58.714
DOCTOR: Have you ordered x-rays?
NURSE: Yes, they're on their way.

04:59.841 --> 05:03.094
-She'll need an urgent CT scan.
-It's organized.

05:04.429 --> 05:06.597
Decerebrate response?

05:06.765 --> 05:08.557
It's her husband.

05:11.728 --> 05:13.396
I want you to talk to her.

05:13.563 --> 05:16.565
[EKG BEEPING]

05:18.443 --> 05:20.319
JOHN:
Rae, it's John.

05:20.487 --> 05:22.405
[BREATHING ON RESPIRATOR]

05:25.575 --> 05:27.243
Try it again.

05:27.577 --> 05:29.453
Rae, it's me.

05:30.998 --> 05:33.124
[ECHOING]
It's John, Rae.

05:40.632 --> 05:42.591
RAE [SINGING]:
Down came the rain

05:42.759 --> 05:45.636
And washed poor Wincy out

05:46.096 --> 05:50.850
Out came the sunshine
And dried up all the rain

05:51.018 --> 05:56.272
And Incy-Wincy spider
Crawled up the spout again

05:57.149 --> 05:59.108
That's a funny one.

05:59.526 --> 06:01.277
Will you try it with Mummy now?

06:01.445 --> 06:02.778
No.

06:02.946 --> 06:04.697
Oh, come on.

06:05.991 --> 06:10.286
RAE [SINGING]:
Incy-Wincy spider

06:10.454 --> 06:13.122
Crawled up the water....

06:13.290 --> 06:14.623
Spout!

06:16.043 --> 06:19.962
Down came the rain
And

06:20.130 --> 06:23.632
BOTH:
Washed poor Wincy out

06:25.802 --> 06:28.804
-Out came the sunshine
-He fell down!

06:29.806 --> 06:33.142
And dried up all the rain

06:33.310 --> 06:34.894
Danny. Danny, come on, darling.

06:35.062 --> 06:37.313
-Get back in your seat.
-I've got him. I saved him.

06:37.481 --> 06:38.814
[TRUCK HORN WAILING]

06:38.982 --> 06:40.357
Danny!

06:40.525 --> 06:41.776
[CAR TIRES SQUEALING]

06:41.943 --> 06:43.194
Danny!

06:43.403 --> 06:45.071
DANNY:
Mommy!

06:45.238 --> 06:47.573
RAE:
No!

06:48.533 --> 06:49.575
[CAR HORNS BLARING]

06:49.910 --> 06:51.911
RAE [SCREAMING]:
No!

06:54.414 --> 06:55.998
No!

06:57.375 --> 06:58.709
No!

07:00.170 --> 07:01.170
[RAE SOBBING]

07:01.338 --> 07:03.839
JOHN:
It's okay. It's all right.

07:08.720 --> 07:12.181
-I was holding him!
-I know, I know.

07:13.141 --> 07:15.017
John, I could smell his head.

07:15.185 --> 07:16.435
Stop it, Rae. Stop it.

07:16.603 --> 07:18.646
No, I can't!

07:19.397 --> 07:22.108
I'm so scared.

07:24.736 --> 07:26.362
I'm so scared.

07:26.530 --> 07:29.532
[WHISPERING]
He's gone. He's gone, baby.

07:29.699 --> 07:32.243
We can never get him back.

07:32.536 --> 07:33.869
Hey.

07:34.037 --> 07:37.081
It's gonna take a long time.

07:38.208 --> 07:40.376
Now, you know that. They warned us.

07:41.878 --> 07:44.296
Let's go home.

07:44.589 --> 07:46.882
-Please?
-It'll be worse there.

07:47.050 --> 07:49.969
-I don't think I can get rid of it.
-Yes, you can.

07:50.137 --> 07:51.554
No, I can't.

07:51.972 --> 07:53.722
Don't say that.

07:53.890 --> 07:55.683
Now, look...

07:58.061 --> 08:00.229
...we've got weeks and weeks.

08:01.148 --> 08:04.275
Calm days, calm seas.

08:04.442 --> 08:06.819
Now, we're gonna get strong.

08:06.987 --> 08:09.155
And when you're strong...

08:09.322 --> 08:12.449
...then we'll go home
and we'll start again.

08:12.617 --> 08:14.451
Won't we, Rae?

08:15.579 --> 08:18.622
Say it, Rae. Won't we?

08:21.710 --> 08:24.044
Say it, Rae. Won't we?

08:29.759 --> 08:31.093
[SIGHS]

08:46.026 --> 08:48.027
[DOG BARKING]

09:03.293 --> 09:04.960
What's wrong, Ben?

09:14.638 --> 09:16.639
[BEN BARKING]

09:27.984 --> 09:29.652
Come on, mate.

09:46.002 --> 09:47.670
[RAE SIGHS]

09:48.880 --> 09:50.547
What was it?

09:51.091 --> 09:53.217
It's nothing. Just the dawn.

09:53.385 --> 09:55.511
Is there any wind?

09:57.722 --> 09:59.390
Not a whisper.

10:50.942 --> 10:54.236
So, what day is it today?

10:54.446 --> 10:58.532
I don't know, Thursday or Friday.
One of those days with an R in it.

11:02.120 --> 11:03.996
Oh, look at that.

11:04.622 --> 11:06.915
First boat in three weeks.

11:14.174 --> 11:16.342
She's been through some weather,
that's for sure.

11:17.635 --> 11:19.428
Is there anybody on deck?

11:19.637 --> 11:21.513
Not that I can see.

11:21.681 --> 11:23.265
I'll call them up.

11:23.433 --> 11:25.934
Oh, do you have to?

11:26.102 --> 11:28.145
I like it like this.

11:28.313 --> 11:30.272
Just the two of us.

11:30.440 --> 11:32.232
So do I.

11:33.443 --> 11:35.277
But look at her, Rae.

11:35.945 --> 11:37.988
That boat's in trouble.

11:55.298 --> 11:57.299
[BEEPING]

12:00.345 --> 12:03.222
Black schooner to my east,
black schooner to my east.

12:03.390 --> 12:06.850
This is yacht Saracen, Victor Kilo 2-7-6-2.

12:07.018 --> 12:11.897
Position 16-16 south, 176-47 west.

12:12.065 --> 12:14.274
Do you read me? Over.

12:38.341 --> 12:40.342
[BEEPING]

12:56.067 --> 12:57.693
John!

13:03.533 --> 13:04.616
John!

13:04.784 --> 13:06.702
BEN: Arf, arf!
JOHN: Whoa.

13:07.203 --> 13:10.414
RAE: I thought I saw something
between here and the boat.

13:10.665 --> 13:12.791
JOHN:
What is it, a turtle?

13:12.959 --> 13:15.294
RAE:
No. It's bigger.

13:22.218 --> 13:24.344
-You see anything?
-Not yet. Hold on.

13:26.931 --> 13:28.557
There it is.

13:29.726 --> 13:31.393
It's a dinghy.

13:32.103 --> 13:33.729
Adrift?

13:34.230 --> 13:36.231
No, there's a man in it.

13:38.651 --> 13:41.653
[MAN GRUNTING]

13:48.077 --> 13:50.078
[BARKING]

14:21.110 --> 14:24.279
JOHN:
Save it! We'll drop down to you!

14:31.871 --> 14:34.498
You hear me? Ship your oars!

14:34.666 --> 14:36.458
Get the fender, darling.

14:39.087 --> 14:40.587
Stand off!

14:47.345 --> 14:49.054
Take it easy.

14:53.977 --> 14:56.562
[PANTING]

15:13.496 --> 15:15.497
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

15:18.376 --> 15:19.626
Get him some water, darling.

15:19.794 --> 15:21.545
-Not too much.
-Okay.

15:23.172 --> 15:25.674
JOHN: Here you are.
-Thanks.

15:30.513 --> 15:32.014
My name is Hughie Warriner.

15:34.851 --> 15:37.352
-John Ingram. My wife, Rae.
-Hi.

15:38.563 --> 15:42.566
I'm 32 days outward bound from Papeete.
I'm heading for Fiji.

15:45.403 --> 15:47.696
I only bought her
about three months ago.

15:48.239 --> 15:50.282
My plan had been
to cruise around the Pacific...

15:50.450 --> 15:53.201
...to sail around the Pacific.

15:53.369 --> 15:55.287
Who would have thought, right?

15:55.455 --> 15:56.830
JOHN:
What's your trouble?

15:56.998 --> 15:59.541
Trouble is she's going down,
that's the trouble.

16:00.251 --> 16:02.753
She's not gonna last the morning.

16:03.630 --> 16:06.715
-Are you sure?
-Yeah, she opened up all over.

16:08.384 --> 16:10.093
Has the water hit your engine?

16:10.261 --> 16:13.013
My engine, the radio...

16:13.181 --> 16:16.099
...the fucking bulkhead. Galleys.

16:16.267 --> 16:18.060
Everything.

16:19.062 --> 16:21.396
My only chance was to try to reach you
in the dinghy.

16:24.776 --> 16:28.904
See what Mr. Warriner needs, darling,
and, um, get him to bed.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.490
RAE:
All right.

16:31.658 --> 16:33.283
Where are you going?

16:34.077 --> 16:37.037
Well, um, I ought to get over there.

16:37.955 --> 16:39.456
How many people onboard?

16:39.624 --> 16:42.501
Nobody. I'm alone. I'm it.

16:44.087 --> 16:48.423
JOHN: You tried to take her
across the Pacific on your own?

16:48.633 --> 16:50.217
HUGHIE:
No.

16:53.137 --> 16:55.347
There were six of us.

16:56.933 --> 16:58.433
[HUGHIE SIGHS]

16:58.601 --> 17:01.311
The others died 10 days ago.

17:04.357 --> 17:06.316
One by one.

17:06.483 --> 17:08.819
It all happened in a day.

17:33.052 --> 17:34.720
What happened?

17:36.264 --> 17:40.308
Have you ever thought about how life
can hinge on the smallest thing?

17:43.354 --> 17:46.732
I mean, ever since I was a kid,
I thought salmon was for cats.

17:47.358 --> 17:49.067
Was it canned salmon?

17:49.902 --> 17:51.653
HUGHIE:
Yeah.

17:55.324 --> 17:58.994
HUGHIE: At first we thought
it was the tourist trots...

17:59.912 --> 18:03.290
...until, uh, Chantal looked at her hand...

18:03.833 --> 18:05.917
...and said Picasso should have painted it.

18:08.838 --> 18:10.422
It had seven fingers.

18:12.300 --> 18:14.259
Double vision, huh?

18:16.679 --> 18:18.764
Sounds like botulism.

18:18.931 --> 18:20.265
What's that?

18:20.433 --> 18:24.352
It's a lethal form of food poisoning.
It hits the nervous system.

18:24.937 --> 18:28.231
Hmm. Yeah, well, I tried everything.

18:29.066 --> 18:30.317
JOHN:
There's no treatment.

18:31.778 --> 18:35.530
Not on a small boat there's not.
Not 1200 miles from land.

18:42.371 --> 18:44.331
Well, ahem...

18:45.041 --> 18:47.250
...when you're ready, Mr. Warriner.

18:52.173 --> 18:53.882
We better go and salvage your gear.

18:55.676 --> 18:59.137
My--? My gear? You're looking at it.

18:59.305 --> 19:01.556
There's nothing to salvage.

19:01.724 --> 19:04.726
Everything was ruined by the water.

19:05.853 --> 19:07.145
There must be something.

19:07.730 --> 19:11.149
Oh, give me a break, will you?
I mean, you know what I had to do?

19:11.567 --> 19:12.984
I can guess.

19:13.152 --> 19:14.402
You can guess.

19:14.570 --> 19:17.197
They've been dead for days.
You know what that does to a body?

19:17.365 --> 19:19.574
You've gotta try and stop
thinking about it.

19:19.742 --> 19:21.535
I mean, I....

19:21.702 --> 19:26.414
Fuck, I can't go back. All right?
I can't go back there right now.

19:27.250 --> 19:28.500
Ever.

19:36.092 --> 19:38.176
That's all right. I understand.

19:39.762 --> 19:42.931
Why don't you go to bed
and get as much sleep as you can?

19:44.767 --> 19:46.268
Thank you.

19:55.278 --> 19:59.030
Look, I'm really sorry to ruin your day,
you know?

20:00.408 --> 20:02.951
-Here?
RAE: Yeah, straight ahead.

20:55.922 --> 20:57.339
JOHN:
You all right?

20:57.506 --> 21:00.008
Yeah. I'm fine.

21:00.176 --> 21:01.426
You sure?

21:01.594 --> 21:02.928
Mm-hm.

21:08.225 --> 21:10.435
Some interesting stuff here.

21:11.228 --> 21:13.021
Listen to this:

21:13.356 --> 21:15.273
"South Sea Island Cruise.

21:15.441 --> 21:17.484
Four young women wanted
for photo assignment.

21:17.652 --> 21:20.570
Must be attractive and broad-minded."

21:23.407 --> 21:25.867
RAE:
You don't like him, do you?

21:27.286 --> 21:28.870
Hadn't really thought about it.

21:29.038 --> 21:31.623
RAE:
John, imagine what he's been through.

21:31.791 --> 21:34.459
JOHN:
I'm sorry, Rae. Whichever way I turn it...

21:35.044 --> 21:36.670
...I just can't swallow it.

21:36.837 --> 21:38.213
Any reason?

21:38.381 --> 21:42.342
Not really. Just 25 years at sea.

22:07.284 --> 22:08.785
Shh.

22:08.953 --> 22:10.537
[WHISPERING]
I'm going onboard her.

22:10.705 --> 22:12.163
[WHISPERING]
You can't do that.

22:12.331 --> 22:14.416
He's fast asleep. He won't even know.

22:14.583 --> 22:16.209
RAE:
He will. He'll hear the engine.

22:16.377 --> 22:18.753
JOHN:
No, he won't. I'll take the dinghy.

22:19.338 --> 22:21.131
Load the gun and keep it with you.

22:21.298 --> 22:22.716
RAE:
Are you serious?

22:22.883 --> 22:25.135
Rae, just do as I say, please.

22:27.430 --> 22:28.930
Okay.

22:43.654 --> 22:46.322
-Back soon.
-Bye.

22:48.617 --> 22:49.868
[BEN BARKS THEN WHIMPERS]

22:55.708 --> 22:57.917
Wait a sec.

22:59.837 --> 23:01.671
Go on, take it.

23:14.935 --> 23:16.436
-One, two....
-Arf!

23:16.604 --> 23:17.937
-Shh. Shh.
-Arf, arf!

23:18.105 --> 23:20.106
[BEN BARKING]

23:27.156 --> 23:28.823
Okay...

23:29.200 --> 23:30.492
...go!

23:35.831 --> 23:37.123
Bring it back. Come on.

24:31.053 --> 24:32.262
[THUD FROM BEHIND]

25:35.409 --> 25:37.076
[WHIMPERS]

26:07.983 --> 26:09.317
[SNIFFS]

26:10.319 --> 26:11.653
Phew.

26:26.835 --> 26:28.336
HUGHIE:
Rae!

26:30.047 --> 26:33.925
Rae, I'm sick! I gotta use the bathroom!

26:34.426 --> 26:37.178
Rae, I'm nauseated. Please.

26:39.682 --> 26:42.684
Rae!
I really don't wanna throw up in here.

26:43.852 --> 26:45.311
Rae!

27:00.369 --> 27:01.703
[SCOFFS]

27:22.224 --> 27:23.224
[WHISPERS]
Shit.

28:10.939 --> 28:12.273
[GRUNTING]

29:03.242 --> 29:04.909
[GRUNTS]

29:15.129 --> 29:17.088
[YELLS]
Jump, Rae! Jump!

29:18.841 --> 29:20.258
Jump!

29:21.552 --> 29:24.178
No. What are you doing?

29:24.721 --> 29:25.888
[GRUNTS]

29:26.056 --> 29:27.390
[GASPS]

29:29.017 --> 29:30.351
HUGHIE:
No.

29:30.602 --> 29:32.270
[RAE SHRIEKS]

29:41.280 --> 29:42.947
Ow! Ow!

29:45.159 --> 29:47.160
[PANTING]

30:08.724 --> 30:10.725
Jump, Rae! Jump!

30:18.734 --> 30:21.736
Get off, Rae! Leave it!

30:25.824 --> 30:27.492
[SPUTTERS]

30:28.744 --> 30:30.077
[GRUNTS]

32:06.967 --> 32:08.467
[ENGINE CHOKES]

32:13.348 --> 32:14.849
Shit.

32:32.909 --> 32:34.910
[BEAMS CREAKING]

33:22.751 --> 33:25.753
[DEEP, RHYTHMIC BREATHING]

33:36.014 --> 33:37.932
[RAPID TICKING]

33:48.068 --> 33:49.402
[MOANS SOFTLY]

33:53.240 --> 33:54.448
[SIGHS]

33:56.952 --> 33:58.285
[GROANS]

34:06.169 --> 34:09.170
["WHO STOLE THE ISOPROPYL ALCOHOL"
PLAYING ON CASSETTE PLAYER]

34:20.058 --> 34:22.643
Oh, Ben.

34:46.293 --> 34:47.626
[GRUNTS]

35:10.358 --> 35:11.692
Where's John?

35:18.700 --> 35:19.700
Now, what?

35:19.868 --> 35:22.036
John, my husband.

35:24.831 --> 35:26.499
Where is he?

35:27.042 --> 35:28.709
He's gone.

35:30.170 --> 35:32.463
Oh, shit.

35:33.048 --> 35:34.632
What have you done to him?

35:36.593 --> 35:38.260
Nothing.

35:38.720 --> 35:40.554
He went onboard her.

35:42.224 --> 35:43.557
We've gotta go back.

35:44.017 --> 35:46.894
Look, he's only got himself
to blame, right?

35:47.062 --> 35:49.063
I mean, he should've trusted me.

35:49.231 --> 35:51.774
But that's always been my problem.

35:51.983 --> 35:55.236
-Don't you understand?
-Please don't shout.

35:55.403 --> 35:57.238
That's always been one of my problems.

35:57.405 --> 36:00.115
I can never tell people's real motives
until it's too late.

36:00.283 --> 36:05.913
Okay. Let's just, uh,
turn the boat around.

36:06.873 --> 36:10.000
-Where shall we go?
-Turn around!

36:10.168 --> 36:12.837
HUGHIE: Hey, look.
You're being very aggressive, Rae.

36:13.004 --> 36:16.423
That could be a problem on this small boat.
I've seen it happen. It doesn't work.

36:16.591 --> 36:17.925
[GRUNTS]

36:33.316 --> 36:36.151
You know, I was watching you
when you were sleeping.

36:37.445 --> 36:40.406
And I gotta tell you
that your face fascinates me.

36:43.618 --> 36:47.454
Yeah. Even when you're 80, Rae,
you'll still be a beautiful woman.

36:53.128 --> 36:55.296
I, uh, studied art for, um....

36:56.131 --> 36:58.966
For a time...

36:59.342 --> 37:02.761
...and something I found is that painters,
when they approach their subjects...

37:02.929 --> 37:07.308
...they always look at the face
from, like, behind, you know?

37:07.475 --> 37:09.643
From the back,
like, to see what's holding it up.

37:09.811 --> 37:11.687
And, uh...

37:12.647 --> 37:15.441
...you've got magnificent bone structure.

37:21.823 --> 37:24.491
God. "Magnificent."
Shit, that sounds like...

37:24.659 --> 37:27.536
...fucking something you'd say
at a cocktail party.

37:29.164 --> 37:31.790
Should have given you my card,
for chrissake.

37:35.045 --> 37:38.088
I just knew we'd get along,
didn't you, Rae?

37:40.926 --> 37:42.259
Hey.

37:44.346 --> 37:45.596
What's wrong?

37:47.557 --> 37:50.809
-Would you just tell me one thing?
-Sure.

37:53.355 --> 37:56.357
I just need to know if that boat is sinking.

37:57.567 --> 37:59.276
Sinking?

38:00.236 --> 38:02.863
-Well, past tense would do, but--
-Oh, God.

38:03.031 --> 38:06.325
But, uh, yeah. Yes, it is.

38:06.493 --> 38:09.703
Why? Uh, don't you believe me?

38:09.871 --> 38:13.791
Yeah. Yeah, I believe you. Of course I do.

38:13.959 --> 38:15.584
-That's why we've gotta go back.
-Back?

38:15.752 --> 38:18.671
-Uh-huh. To get John.
-What, you mean back there?

38:18.838 --> 38:20.422
Yeah.

38:20.590 --> 38:22.716
-Right now.
-Uh-huh.

38:24.010 --> 38:27.471
No, Rae, no. Okay? That's over.
That's all over.

38:27.639 --> 38:30.724
So why don't we just erase that one
from memory and start again, please?

38:30.892 --> 38:32.726
There's no going back, Rae.

38:32.894 --> 38:35.646
No. No, don't say that.

38:35.814 --> 38:37.314
He's gonna drown, Hughie.

38:37.482 --> 38:39.566
There you go.
Now you're ruining it again.

38:39.734 --> 38:41.485
That boat is sinking.

38:41.653 --> 38:43.153
That's not my fault.

38:45.323 --> 38:48.575
What about those people, huh?

38:50.120 --> 38:52.413
There wasn't any food poisoning,
was there?

38:58.086 --> 39:00.170
You wanna do this now?

39:01.047 --> 39:02.715
All right.

39:03.299 --> 39:05.551
They tried to kill me, Rae.

39:05.760 --> 39:09.513
They tried to suck the light out of me,
if you can possibly grasp that concept.

39:09.681 --> 39:11.765
-Who were?
-All of them.

39:11.933 --> 39:13.600
Look....

39:13.768 --> 39:15.602
Nobody wants to kill you, Hughie--

39:15.770 --> 39:18.772
What? Repeat that.

39:18.940 --> 39:21.859
-I said, nobody--
-Say the words, Rae. Come on.

39:22.027 --> 39:23.777
-You mean I just imagined it.
-No.

39:23.945 --> 39:25.863
-No?
-No.

39:26.114 --> 39:28.073
I just meant that it must be a mistake.

39:28.241 --> 39:30.200
A mistake? Lady...

39:30.368 --> 39:32.536
...the mistake is that you think
I'm making this up.

39:32.704 --> 39:34.913
No! No. No, I don't.

39:35.081 --> 39:38.250
You sound so much like them, Rae,
it's scary.

39:39.002 --> 39:42.379
Now, they were trying to kill me.
Do you understand?

39:43.131 --> 39:44.798
Yeah.

39:45.967 --> 39:48.093
Yeah, I understand.

41:07.132 --> 41:09.133
[ENGINE CHOKES]

41:17.142 --> 41:18.475
[ENGINE TURNING]

41:21.229 --> 41:22.521
[GIRL GIGGLING ON TV]

41:35.034 --> 41:37.035
[MUSIC PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ON TV]

41:56.181 --> 41:57.848
RUSSELL [ON TV]:
Come on, turn around.

41:58.016 --> 41:59.766
Don't look at the bloody boat.
Look at me.

41:59.934 --> 42:02.644
GIRL [ON TV]:
Okay, I'm sorry.

42:06.149 --> 42:10.152
Oh, what are you doing, Hughie?
Go away.

42:10.945 --> 42:13.113
RUSSELL:
Okay, ladies, forget the home movie.

42:13.281 --> 42:17.576
HUGHIE [ON TV]: Listen, if you turn around,
you can get these incredible silhouettes.

42:17.744 --> 42:20.454
When I want your advice
on how to take photographs, I'll ask you.

42:20.622 --> 42:22.206
Until then, keep your mouth shut.

42:22.373 --> 42:25.042
HUGHIE [ON TV]: I'll remember that,
but for now, Russell, please.

42:25.210 --> 42:28.712
If you move two steps to your left,
I can get you with the boat.

42:28.880 --> 42:31.798
We'll look at this someday and laugh.
Trust me. This is really good.

42:32.550 --> 42:35.802
RUSSELL [ON TV]: For God's sake, Hughie.
Get that bloody camera off me.

42:35.970 --> 42:39.139
I take the pictures, Hughie, baby.
You dance, I shoot.

42:39.307 --> 42:42.392
HUGHIE [ON TV]:
What the fuck is your problem?

43:43.621 --> 43:45.163
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

43:49.377 --> 43:51.044
[MUTTERING]

43:53.464 --> 43:56.675
Must be the same old thing.

43:59.470 --> 44:02.472
["NO-MAD"
PLAYING ON CASSETTE PLAYER]

44:03.057 --> 44:04.391
[BEN WHIMPERS]

44:05.518 --> 44:07.477
This is stereo, Ben.

44:10.398 --> 44:12.232
Low production...

44:16.571 --> 44:17.571
Survey says....

44:17.739 --> 44:19.072
[BEN BARKS]

44:23.661 --> 44:24.995
[BEN BARKS]

44:27.540 --> 44:28.874
[BEEPING]

44:29.042 --> 44:30.500
[WHISPERS]
Come on.

44:33.004 --> 44:34.504
[BEEPING]

44:44.432 --> 44:46.433
[BEN BARKING]

44:48.019 --> 44:49.061
Forty-two miles....

44:49.228 --> 44:52.981
Saracen, Saracen, this is Orpheus.
Do you read me? Over.

44:59.781 --> 45:01.782
[STATIC OVER RADIO]

45:05.995 --> 45:07.621
Saracen, Saracen, this is--

45:07.789 --> 45:09.790
[STATIC OVER RADIO]

45:14.379 --> 45:15.545
[BEN BARKS]

45:26.974 --> 45:28.308
John?

45:30.436 --> 45:31.478
Yes.

45:33.481 --> 45:34.648
John?

45:35.942 --> 45:37.067
Are you okay?

45:38.945 --> 45:40.153
Are you there?

45:41.155 --> 45:44.866
Yes, Rae, I'm here. I'm here.
Can you hear me?

45:45.701 --> 45:47.661
RAE [OVER RADIO]:
Are you there?

45:49.205 --> 45:51.331
Rae, it's me.

45:53.876 --> 45:55.669
I'm not reading you.

45:57.839 --> 45:59.339
[STATIC OVER RADIO]

45:59.507 --> 46:01.049
Is that you, John?

46:06.889 --> 46:08.181
Are you hurt?

46:12.186 --> 46:14.855
RAE [OVER RADIO]:
What about the boat? It's sinking, isn't it?

46:15.898 --> 46:17.899
[TWO CLICKS OVER RADIO]

46:19.527 --> 46:20.694
So that's it.

46:20.862 --> 46:24.030
No, you're not hurt
and, no, the boat isn't sinking.

46:24.198 --> 46:25.449
Is that right?

46:29.912 --> 46:31.788
Are you following?

46:32.540 --> 46:34.541
[ONE CLICK OVER RADIO]

46:36.002 --> 46:37.210
John, what should I do?

46:37.837 --> 46:41.214
I can't make him turn around.
He just won't.

46:42.717 --> 46:44.885
Do you want me to stop the boat?

46:48.681 --> 46:51.725
RAE [OVER RADIO]:
Oh, I don't know how.

46:53.102 --> 46:54.144
Come on.

46:56.606 --> 46:57.939
Look...

46:58.691 --> 47:00.442
...don't worry.

47:00.610 --> 47:02.694
I'll work it out.

47:12.788 --> 47:15.582
You'll be here soon, won't you?

47:34.101 --> 47:36.102
[BEEPING]

47:55.498 --> 47:58.375
["NEW YORK TURNPIKE"
PLAYING ON CASSETTE PLAYER]

48:36.664 --> 48:37.998
[SCREAMS]

48:48.009 --> 48:50.010
[MOTOR STOPS]

49:32.887 --> 49:34.888
[FOOTSTEPS ABOVE]

49:38.351 --> 49:39.684
[BEN BARKS]

49:41.395 --> 49:43.021
Oh.

49:43.189 --> 49:46.232
Score one for Mrs. Ingram.
She has a hell of a season ahead of her.

49:54.533 --> 49:56.201
Ben, no!

49:58.079 --> 49:59.579
No, Ben.

49:59.747 --> 50:01.081
Leave it.

50:03.626 --> 50:06.336
-Just leave it there.
-Fetch, Ben. Come on, bring it here, boy.

50:06.504 --> 50:08.296
RAE: All right, bring it here.
-Stay, Ben.

50:08.464 --> 50:10.840
RAE: Come on.
-Tread right there.

50:11.008 --> 50:14.511
RAE: Okay, drop it. Drop the key.
-Hold the key, Ben.

50:14.679 --> 50:15.929
RAE: No, drop it.
-Keep it, boy.

50:16.097 --> 50:17.263
RAE:
Over here, then. Come on.

50:17.431 --> 50:19.683
Stay, Ben. Tread.

50:20.101 --> 50:22.560
-Backstroke.
-Come on, Ben.

50:23.145 --> 50:24.813
Come on.

50:25.231 --> 50:26.564
Aah!

50:30.444 --> 50:33.196
That's beautiful bone structure there, Rae.

50:35.366 --> 50:37.033
Come on.

50:43.833 --> 50:46.418
Good boy. He's a champ, this one.

50:46.585 --> 50:48.795
Jump, Ben. Up. Come on, climb.

50:48.963 --> 50:50.296
Whoa!

51:01.308 --> 51:03.309
That's the way.

51:09.066 --> 51:10.608
Thank you.

51:16.073 --> 51:17.115
[CABIN DOOR BANGS]

52:32.775 --> 52:34.234
Friends?

52:38.572 --> 52:39.906
Yeah.

52:40.741 --> 52:42.075
Friends.

52:54.421 --> 52:56.422
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

52:56.590 --> 52:57.590
Come talk to me.

52:57.758 --> 53:00.176
RUSSELL [ON TV]:
Come on, simple man. The camera's rolling.

53:00.344 --> 53:05.223
Forget the fucking vibe. Lose that.
Talk to me, Russell. Who are you?

53:05.391 --> 53:09.352
RUSSELL [ON TV]: Come on, drop the veil.
Drop the veil, sucker. Drop your guts.

53:09.520 --> 53:14.649
HUGHIE [ON TV]: I got the picture.
Vietnam, Laos, Castro, Cambodia.

53:14.817 --> 53:17.902
Russell Bellows,
big, brave war photographer.

53:18.070 --> 53:20.864
The man on the edge
capturing the face of death.

53:21.031 --> 53:25.785
But now, no, now,
appearing with his five new refugees.

53:25.953 --> 53:29.330
RUSSELL [ON TV]: Yes, that's right.
HUGHIE: Five suckers on a sinking boat.

53:29.498 --> 53:31.791
The ultimate session. Moral decay.

53:31.959 --> 53:35.420
What 60-minute wet dreams are made of,
am I right?

53:35.588 --> 53:38.298
Come on in, Russ. The water's great.

53:38.465 --> 53:41.301
You got the bloated head.
How about the bloated belly?

53:41.468 --> 53:44.762
Come out from behind that camera, Russell.
Come out from behind that camera.

54:54.249 --> 54:55.541
RAE [OVER RADIO]:
John.

55:03.968 --> 55:06.010
John, can you hear me?

55:10.057 --> 55:13.309
Saracen to black schooner.
Come in, please.

55:16.939 --> 55:18.898
Come in, please.

55:19.066 --> 55:21.067
[HUGHIE YELLING INDISTINCTLY ON TV]

55:23.612 --> 55:24.904
John.

55:25.072 --> 55:26.823
John, it's me.

55:28.784 --> 55:31.411
I got the key up onto the deck, but he....

55:34.331 --> 55:36.624
[RAPID CLICKING OVER RADIO]

55:36.792 --> 55:38.751
What's wrong? Are you hurt?

55:43.298 --> 55:44.590
Is it the boat?

55:46.760 --> 55:48.553
John, is it sinking?

55:48.721 --> 55:50.388
[ONE CLICK OVER RADIO]

55:53.600 --> 55:54.767
Okay.

55:55.519 --> 55:58.354
How long? Hours?

56:01.859 --> 56:03.609
RAE [OVER RADIO]:
How many? Two?

56:04.445 --> 56:06.446
[TWO CLICKS OVER RADIO]

56:08.323 --> 56:09.907
Four?

56:10.075 --> 56:12.076
[TWO CLICKS OVER RADIO]

56:13.120 --> 56:14.620
RAE [OVER RADIO]:
John, six?

56:14.788 --> 56:17.373
HUGHIE [ON TV]:
I've drained you of your power, Russell.

56:17.541 --> 56:19.542
-You've lost.
RAE [OVER RADIO]: John?

56:19.710 --> 56:20.960
HUGHIE [ON TV]:
Good night!

56:21.128 --> 56:22.128
[GIRLS SCREAMING ON TV]

56:25.090 --> 56:26.549
Six?

56:26.717 --> 56:28.718
[ONE CLICK OVER RADIO]

56:32.639 --> 56:33.973
Six.

56:35.184 --> 56:36.851
Okay.

56:37.686 --> 56:40.063
I'm gonna be there by sunset.

56:41.565 --> 56:43.566
[HUGHIE YELLING INDISTINCTLY ON TV]

56:43.901 --> 56:45.234
[GIRLS SCREAMING ON TV]

56:45.402 --> 56:47.403
[MOTOR AND TV STOP]

56:58.248 --> 56:59.749
John.

57:01.794 --> 57:03.628
I love you.

57:05.589 --> 57:06.923
[RADAR BEEPING]

57:11.345 --> 57:13.012
John.

57:16.850 --> 57:18.518
John.

57:20.896 --> 57:23.981
John, answer me, please. Answer me.

57:27.319 --> 57:29.320
John, do you read me?

57:31.448 --> 57:32.824
John.

57:34.076 --> 57:36.410
John, please.

58:28.255 --> 58:29.589
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

01:00:57.612 --> 01:00:58.946
[RAE GASPS]

01:01:03.118 --> 01:01:04.452
[HUGHIE MOANS]

01:01:06.621 --> 01:01:07.955
Oh.

01:01:08.123 --> 01:01:10.750
I've just gotta go to the bathroom.

01:01:11.668 --> 01:01:13.544
You gotta--? Uh-huh.

01:01:14.046 --> 01:01:15.713
-Sorry.
-Ha.

01:01:16.465 --> 01:01:19.550
Gotta do what you gotta do.

01:01:49.206 --> 01:01:50.247
Hmm.

01:02:03.470 --> 01:02:05.596
[BARKING]

01:02:06.640 --> 01:02:08.099
RAE: Shh!
-Hello?

01:02:10.227 --> 01:02:11.602
Rae?

01:02:16.483 --> 01:02:17.483
For later.

01:02:17.651 --> 01:02:20.152
Uh, yeah, I was gonna say
you read my mind.

01:02:40.048 --> 01:02:42.049
HUGHIE [WHISPERS]:
Friends, Rae.

01:02:42.968 --> 01:02:44.635
[HUGHIE LAUGHS]

01:02:51.852 --> 01:02:53.185
[DOOR OPENS]

01:02:55.897 --> 01:02:59.191
-I better put him up on the deck.
-Don't worry. Get out of here.

01:02:59.359 --> 01:03:01.193
No. I better put him up--

01:03:01.361 --> 01:03:04.989
Shh. Come on. Ben, go away.

01:03:08.034 --> 01:03:10.161
[WHIMPERS]

01:03:17.794 --> 01:03:19.795
[GRUNTING]

01:03:24.092 --> 01:03:25.634
[RAE GASPS]

01:04:38.583 --> 01:04:40.584
[WHISTLING]

01:05:00.772 --> 01:05:03.774
[GRUNTING]

01:06:03.418 --> 01:06:06.295
-Where are you going?
-To get a drink.

01:06:06.463 --> 01:06:07.796
Mm.

01:06:26.900 --> 01:06:28.567
HUGHIE:
Isn't this great?

01:06:29.402 --> 01:06:32.112
-What?
-These lemons, they're just....

01:06:32.989 --> 01:06:35.741
Cruising around the South Pacific,
just the two of us.

01:06:35.909 --> 01:06:38.327
-Yup.
-Yup.

01:06:41.498 --> 01:06:42.956
How do I look?

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:45.751
-Great.
-How do I smell?

01:06:45.919 --> 01:06:47.586
-Uh....
-Uh-huh.

01:06:47.754 --> 01:06:49.922
Thank you for your honesty.

01:06:56.262 --> 01:06:59.556
Nope, no, no, no.

01:07:00.433 --> 01:07:05.270
What's missing from my life at this moment
are the soothing sounds of...

01:07:06.606 --> 01:07:10.150
...Julio Iglesias, Joni Mitchell
and The Broadway Album.

01:07:10.318 --> 01:07:13.570
What, Rae, did you get these tapes
thrown in free with the knives?

01:07:14.155 --> 01:07:15.614
He finds it. Yes.

01:07:22.956 --> 01:07:24.957
["THE LION SLEEPS TONIGHT"
PLAYING ON RADIO]

01:08:14.340 --> 01:08:15.716
That looks good.

01:08:15.884 --> 01:08:18.343
Mm. Mm, it is.

01:08:18.511 --> 01:08:19.845
Mm, mm.

01:08:22.557 --> 01:08:23.932
-Do you want some?
-No.

01:08:24.100 --> 01:08:26.143
-No, come on.
-Mm-mm. No thanks.

01:08:26.310 --> 01:08:28.937
-You do. Come on, have it.
-Now, look....

01:08:29.104 --> 01:08:30.354
Do you want it?

01:08:30.523 --> 01:08:31.857
I want it.

01:08:32.024 --> 01:08:33.399
Thank you.

01:08:36.946 --> 01:08:38.988
I better go and get dressed.

01:08:40.533 --> 01:08:43.327
Keep it. Make me another one.

01:09:22.242 --> 01:09:24.076
HUGHIE:
Room service.

01:09:31.292 --> 01:09:33.919
There's a squall coming.
We better get the canopy down.

01:09:34.546 --> 01:09:36.255
Okay.

01:10:20.758 --> 01:10:22.759
[JOHN BANGING AGAINST DOOR]

01:10:28.182 --> 01:10:30.183
[GRUNTING]

01:10:40.278 --> 01:10:42.279
[PANTING]

01:10:52.957 --> 01:10:54.291
Oh, shit.

01:10:59.964 --> 01:11:01.632
What?

01:11:04.677 --> 01:11:06.720
Friends, Rae?

01:11:06.888 --> 01:11:07.930
[YELLS]
Friends?

01:11:11.935 --> 01:11:13.936
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:11:16.773 --> 01:11:19.024
Let go.

01:11:20.360 --> 01:11:22.361
-Unh!
-Come on.

01:11:33.373 --> 01:11:34.998
[RAE GASPS]

01:12:11.077 --> 01:12:12.661
HUGHIE:
Good night!

01:12:28.052 --> 01:12:29.386
[HUGHIE GRUNTS]

01:12:57.081 --> 01:12:59.082
[GROANING]

01:13:42.627 --> 01:13:43.794
[RAE GASPS]

01:13:43.961 --> 01:13:45.295
[HUGHIE HISSING]

01:14:30.675 --> 01:14:32.551
[RAE PANTING]

01:14:41.060 --> 01:14:42.894
Okay.

01:14:44.772 --> 01:14:46.773
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

01:18:17.193 --> 01:18:19.194
[JOHN POUNDING ON DOOR]

01:18:38.631 --> 01:18:40.632
[JOHN GASPING]

01:20:09.805 --> 01:20:11.806
[GASPING]

01:22:59.308 --> 01:23:01.392
[YELLS]

01:23:26.001 --> 01:23:27.377
Don't make me.

01:23:28.754 --> 01:23:31.005
No one's gonna make you.

01:23:31.173 --> 01:23:32.840
Stay there!

01:23:33.008 --> 01:23:34.926
HUGHIE:
I just wanna talk.

01:24:48.292 --> 01:24:49.625
[GROANS]

01:24:51.086 --> 01:24:52.754
[HUGHIE GRUNTS]

01:26:38.610 --> 01:26:39.944
[SIGHS]

01:28:07.908 --> 01:28:10.076
RAE:
I found you.

01:30:43.146 --> 01:30:45.189
Fresh water.

01:30:45.690 --> 01:30:47.817
That's extravagant.

01:30:48.276 --> 01:30:50.611
No, you wanna hear extravagant?

01:30:50.779 --> 01:30:51.821
Yeah.

01:30:53.240 --> 01:30:55.491
A steaming hot bath...

01:30:56.243 --> 01:30:59.286
...that you can slip into up to your ears...

01:30:59.538 --> 01:31:02.123
...with coffee and a croissant.

01:31:02.290 --> 01:31:04.375
A croissant.

01:31:04.543 --> 01:31:06.043
Covered in...

01:31:06.336 --> 01:31:08.671
...bitter and dark marmalade.

01:31:08.839 --> 01:31:10.422
Oh.

01:31:10.590 --> 01:31:12.258
And mango.

01:31:12.467 --> 01:31:14.677
Really, really cold.

01:31:14.845 --> 01:31:16.011
Mm. Now you're talking.

01:31:16.179 --> 01:31:18.180
[KETTLE WHISTLING]

01:31:33.280 --> 01:31:34.613
[KETTLE STOPS WHISTLING]

01:31:58.972 --> 01:32:00.306
[MOANS SOFTLY]

01:32:00.974 --> 01:32:03.517
You know what I'd love for lunch?

01:32:04.644 --> 01:32:07.605
Fresh asparagus.

01:32:08.315 --> 01:32:10.316
Then, um...

01:32:10.692 --> 01:32:12.443
...pasta.

01:32:12.944 --> 01:32:15.779
Angel-hair pasta.

01:32:16.114 --> 01:32:21.619
With heaps of basil and garlic and olive oil.

01:32:22.329 --> 01:32:25.664
And, um...

01:32:25.999 --> 01:32:27.791
...ah, apple pie.

01:32:28.543 --> 01:32:30.044
Yeah.

01:32:30.212 --> 01:32:32.713
Uh, John...

01:32:32.881 --> 01:32:34.798
...have you got the towel?

01:32:36.551 --> 01:32:38.552
[RAE GASPS]

01:32:57.906 --> 01:32:59.240
[HUGHIE GROANS]

01:36:16.438 --> 01:36:18.439
[ENGLISH SDH]
